The paper deals with designing a mechanism for fair and efficient distribution of resources in the presence of strategic agents, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The mechanism involves statistical tests and decision functions, which are common tools in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with the allocation of goods, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT).
